6. Save File Risk And Backups

Editing save files can damage, corrupt, invalidate, or permanently break save files.

Some games use checksums, encryption, compression, cloud synchronization, version checks, or other protection systems. A game may reject, overwrite, delete, or fail to load a modified save.

NOXLAB SEWIZARD includes backup features, but you are responsible for making and keeping backups before editing any file. You should also keep separate external backups for important saves.

noxian0 is not responsible if:

- a save file is damaged;
- a save file becomes unusable;
- game progress is lost;
- a game rejects a modified save;
- a cloud save overwrites a local save;
- a backup is missing, deleted, overwritten, or unusable;
- the user did not make a backup using the app or outside the app;
- the user edits the wrong file;
- the user ignores warnings or uses unsupported formats.

Use the software at your own risk.

7. Unsupported Formats

NOXLAB SEWIZARD may detect, display, or inspect save files that it cannot safely edit.

If a save format is unknown, encrypted, compressed, checksum-protected, binary, or unsupported, the software should be treated as a viewer/backup tool only unless proper support exists.

You are responsible for verifying that any edited save works correctly before relying on it.

